edu.ucsc.cross.hse.core.model

Interface HybridDynamics<X>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    HybridSystem

    public interface HybridDynamics<X>
    This interface defines the syste state as the parameter X, and outlines the methods that must be implemented to define a hybrid dynamical model of the form documented in the user manual.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean C(X x)
      The flow set is the set of states that define the continuous domain, which is where the system exhibits discrete continuous dynamics.
      boolean D(X x)
      The jump set is the set of states that define the discrete domain, which is where the system exhibits discrete discrete dynamics.
      void F(X x, X x_dot)
      The flow map is a mapping that determines the continuous dynamics of the state.
      void G(X x, X x_plus)
      The jump map is a mapping that determines the discrete changes that occur to the state variable.

    • Method Detail

      • C

        boolean C(X x)
        The flow set is the set of states that define the continuous domain, which is where the system exhibits discrete continuous dynamics. This function returns true if the state is in the flow set, or false if not
        Parameters:
        x - the current state of the system

      • F

        void F(X x,
       X x_dot)
        The flow map is a mapping that determines the continuous dynamics of the state. This function defines how to compute the derivatives of the state elements
        Parameters:
        x - the current state of the system
        x_dot - a copy of the state where the computed derivatives are to be stored.

      • D

        boolean D(X x)
        The jump set is the set of states that define the discrete domain, which is where the system exhibits discrete discrete dynamics. This function returns true if the state is in the jump set, or false if not

      • G

        void G(X x,
       X x_plus)
        The jump map is a mapping that determines the discrete changes that occur to the state variable. This function defines how the state values change discretely
        Parameters:
        x - the current state of the system
        x_dot - a copy of the state where the updated jump state is to be stored
